---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="DEVS — Terms of Service" description="Terms of Service for DEVS (begindevs.com).">
  <main id="main" class="px-6 py-32 md:py-40">
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose-legal">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the DEVS platform
        operated at <a href="https://begindevs.com">begindevs.com</a> ("the
        Service"), provided by DEVS ("we," "us," or "our"). By using the
        Service, you agree to these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What DEVS Is</h2>
      <p>
        DEVS is an online skills training platform that provides interactive,
        browser-based practice environments for software development team
        workflows. DEVS is <strong>not</strong> an accredited educational
        institution. We do not grant degrees, diplomas, certificates, or
        professional credentials. Completion of DEVS labs or projects does not
        constitute a formal qualification.
      </p>

      <h2>2. No Employment Guarantees</h2>
      <p>
        DEVS is designed to help you practice team delivery skills. We make no
        guarantees regarding employment outcomes, job placement, salary levels,
        or career advancement. Any references to interview preparation,
        portfolio building, or hiring readiness describe the intended purpose
        of the training, not guaranteed results.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Accounts</h2>
      <p>
        You must provide accurate information when creating an account. You are
        responsible for maintaining the security of your account credentials. You
        must be at least 13 years old to use the Service.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Subscriptions and Billing</h2>
      <p>
        DEVS plans to offer Free, Pro, and Founding Member tiers. Specific
        billing terms, including pricing, renewal, cancellation, and refund
        policies, will be detailed here before paid subscriptions become
        available. No payment is required to join the early access list.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Service</li>
        <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service or its infrastructure</li>
        <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or extract source code from the Service</li>
        <li>Resell, sublicense, or redistribute access to the Service</li>
        <li>Use automated tools to scrape content or data from the Service</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Your Content</h2>
      <p>
        Code you write within DEVS labs is yours. We do not claim ownership of
        your code, commit messages, PR descriptions, or other content you create
        within the platform. However, by using the public profile feature, you
        grant us a license to display your delivery record data (project names,
        stats, skills) on your public profile page.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        The DEVS platform, including lab content, reviewer personas, UI design,
        and documentation, is our intellectual property. You may not copy,
        modify, distribute, or create derivative works from our content without
        written permission.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Availability and Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We strive to keep the Service available but do not guarantee
        uninterrupted access. We may modify, suspend, or discontinue features at
        any time. We will provide reasonable notice for significant changes that
        affect paid subscribers.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, DEVS is provided "as is" without
        warranties of any kind. We are not liable for indirect, incidental,
        special, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Service.
        Our total liability to you shall not exceed the amount you paid us in the
        12 months preceding the claim.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Termination</h2>
      <p>
        We may suspend or terminate your account if you violate these Terms. You
        may delete your account at any time. Upon deletion, your personal data
        will be removed in accordance with our
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of
        material changes by email or by posting a notice on the Service.
        Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the United States. Any disputes
        shall be resolved in the courts of the state in which DEVS is
        incorporated.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        A dedicated contact email will be provided when the full platform
        launches.
      </p>

      <div class="back-link">
        <nav class="legal-links" aria-label="Legal page links">
          <a href="/">&larr; Back to DEVS</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="/terms" aria-current="page">Terms of Service</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-legal {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .prose-legal h1 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prose-legal .meta {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .prose-legal h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .prose-legal p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .prose-legal ul {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .prose-legal li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .prose-legal a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .prose-legal a:hover {
    color: white;
  }
  .back-link {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
  }
  .back-link a {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .back-link a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .legal-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .legal-links span {
    opacity: 0.45;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }
</style>
